On the other hand, for several years, one of the operators distributed free SIM start-ups to tourists at airports.
They were completely anonymous.
Ten telecom regulators from other Asian countries, including Malaysia and Singapore, are considering introducing the same measure as Thailand.
They also currently have a mandatory SIM registration, but legal use of the tracking system is not possible.
However, the planned measure does not imply an obligation for foreigners to acquire a local operator upon entering the SIM country.
Of course, they can use roaming services with their own home SIM, in which case the Thai authorities will be short on them.
Operators of a given country, after crossing the border, i.e. after logging SIM to their network, only know the relevant network information.
They know the phone number, but not the information about the owner.
However, the difference in roaming prices compared to the rates of local operators is so glaring that most tourists during their stay in Thailand begin to look for local SIMs.
The authorities’ efforts to monitor the movement of foreigners have been met with immediate criticism from foreigners living in Thailand.
Tantasith calms the situation and compares the planned system to the obligation to provide a residential address in immigration documents in connection with the protection of privacy.
In addition, if necessary, the police will need a court order to monitor a particular person.
Any abuse of the system will be subject to an unspecified penalty.
“If the service provider tracks the SIM’s location without a court order, it will be charged with a crime,” Tantasith added.
In addition, the system should maximize the use of prepaid cards.
While there is currently a recycling of a specific number after the 90-day period after which the SIM did not log in to the network, the number could now be renewed after 15 days if you leave Thailand.
Luxury apartment in a new building in Vinohrady has a swimming pool and a hot tub on the terrace.
Why did you choose an apartment in a new building?
