Why did you just address them?
Would you recommend working with an expert to anyone?
We would recommend cooperation with an architect to everyone, if he proposes an apartment from the beginning, because it is a very complex technical process.
The second level is the interior design itself: designers have a significantly better idea of the range of possible materials and, based on the client's wishes, are able to properly harmonize the interior.
We worked with the architect Lenka Langerová on our mountain apartment, then based on the personal recommendation of another client, and since everything worked well, it was a clear choice for us during the reconstruction of our new apartment in Vinohrady.
What were your practical and aesthetic requirements?
We wanted a generous social-residential space with adequate facilities for a family of four conceived as a modern, but not cold interior.
