Were there any complications during the implementation, due to which you had to give up the original ideas, or, conversely, proceed to new ones?
Perhaps only in the initial phase of the project, when we came to the building at the moment when it was first possible to climb to the height of our floor, and found that the views that we planned, in fact, shade the surrounding buildings.
Then we literally changed the layout overnight from the ground up.
Granite was used on the kitchen line and on the lining of the fireplace wall.
The interior is dominated by wooden surfaces complemented by leather, for example, the upholstery of Norma dining and bar chairs from Arper.
How would you characterize the interior?
