No one can accuse the courier of not delivering the shipment when in fact he delivered it, the receipt and delivery are verified using QR codes.
Are there any restrictions?
Whether in relation to the size or content of the package?
You can transport anything.
We have three sizes, small as a cube of butter, medium as a plate of eggs and large as a bass beer.
After that, there are no more restrictions and if someone has a place in the car, they will move the refrigerator.
Plus, the sender has the option to take a picture of the package in the application, so the courier can see what he wants.
