Later I found out that they were meeting at his house, in the laundry room.
How many times did I know they were there?
I got the keys, he was determined to catch them there.
I don’t know why, but I always stayed home.
I've never been able to go in there, take that decisive step.
You may laugh at me, but I believe that my wife controlled me mentally.
I think she soon found out that I was manageable, that I was going to do what she wanted.
And I really did.
Maybe I'm just a piece of work.
My neighbors told me that they knew about it too.
I was so stupid, I never asked them what to do.
I was afraid that if it all broke, it would be bad.
That it would affect everyone in the family, only the daughter suspected something.
So I always put it off, go on and on.
But one day I went to his apartment to see if I needed help with anything in the laundry room.
He went there with me, and I told him that I got an anonymous tip, that he was seeing my wife, and that it was all there.
I asked him what he would tell me.
He stood there, shrugging his shoulders, looking at the ground without saying a word.
Then I also met his wife on the way out of the store at the time.
I told her, but she didn't believe it.
She didn't respond, and she didn't tell me anything.
No one told me anything at the time.
I'm the kind of person who's never been anywhere, who's having trouble getting to know someone, let alone finding a woman.
I didn’t even think about divorce.
I always hoped it would end one day.
I thought I'd forgive her and life would go on.
It wasn't like that.
