At home, she always did everything - cooking, washing, cleaning.
She's hard-working.
She always tried to give me no other reason to complain.
And you could say she's kind.
But sometimes I want to caress her, hug her, and she won't let go.
We go for walks and shopping together and everyone thinks what a happy marriage we have.
But she once told me that she never loved me.
That she loved me and she loved me, but she didn't love me.
